<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 11:00PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Convective showers with gusty winds will impact portions of
Liberty, southeastern Toole, Blaine, Hill and northern Chouteau
Counties through MIDNIGHT MDT...
At 1059 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty winds along a line
extending from 27 miles north of Chester to near The Knees.
Movement was east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Havre, Fort Benton, Chinook, Chester, Big Sandy, Harlem, Parker
School, Beaver Creek, Lothair, Joplin, Hays, The Knees, Azure,
Inverness, Agency, St. Pierre, Gildford, Sangrey, Boneau and Fort
Belknap.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
